define({"topics":[{"title":"Add or Replace a Signed Certificate on an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> for <span class=\"ph\">Conductor<\/span> Communication","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, the <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span> come with a <span class=\"ph\">Tempered<\/span> factory-installed         certificate. You can add your own custom CA certificate to use for <span class=\"ph\">Conductor<\/span> communication. <\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/aw_custom_certs.html","attributes":{"data-id":"cond_custom_certs_signed"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"cond_custom_certs_signed-d10823e10858","next":"cond_custom_certs_signed-d10823e10858"},{"title":"Set up Port Groups on an Airwall Gateway","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The default port groups work for some deployments. You may need to set up <span class=\"ph\">underlay<\/span> or <span class=\"ph\">overlay<\/span> port groups if         your deployment requires it.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/port_groups.html","attributes":{"data-id":"port_groups"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"port_groups-d10823e10933","next":"port_groups-d10823e10933"},{"title":"Local Bypass","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">With local bypass you can separate traffic (split tunnel) going through your <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span>, where you         selectively encrypt and tunnel some traffic, while allowing other traffic to pass through         the <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> unchanged.         This ability also allows protected devices to securely communicate with devices or network         locations that are not protected by <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Edge Services<\/span>.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/seamless_bypass.html","attributes":{"data-id":"seamless_bypass"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"seamless_bypass-d10823e11165","next":"seamless_bypass-d10823e11165"},{"title":"Backhaul Bypass","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Set up backhaul bypass to allow any v3.0 or later <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> to reach         bypass destinations by tunneling traffic using designated bypass egress <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span>. Optionally, you         can use a regional backhaul bypass pool for <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span> that support         backhaul bypass and are not gateways themselves. See <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https:\/\/usc-word-edit.officeapps.live.com\/we\/wordeditorframe.aspx?ui=en%2DGB&amp;rs=en%2DUS&amp;wopisrc=https%3A%2F%2Ftemperednetworks.sharepoint.com%2Fsites%2FTechDocsTeam%2F_vti_bin%2Fwopi.ashx%2Ffiles%2F756bf4796bf34a40a861ad39780652ca&amp;wdenableroaming=1&amp;mscc=1&amp;hid=0A1B9BA0-C06A-3000-46EB-F87A46E9F86A&amp;wdorigin=ItemsView&amp;wdhostclicktime=1677713460786&amp;jsapi=1&amp;jsapiver=v1&amp;newsession=1&amp;corrid=4eee062c-84b6-4df0-a903-5295a5347fd8&amp;usid=4eee062c-84b6-4df0-a903-5295a5347fd8&amp;sftc=1&amp;cac=1&amp;mtf=1&amp;sfp=1&amp;instantedit=1&amp;wopicomplete=1&amp;wdredirectionreason=Unified_SingleFlush&amp;rct=Normal&amp;ctp=LeastProtected&amp;_Region_Bypass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external noopener\">Region Bypass<\/a>.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/backhaul_bypass.html","attributes":{"data-id":"backhaul_bypass"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"backhaul_bypass-d10823e11222","next":"backhaul_bypass-d10823e11222"},{"title":"Enable DNS lookup for bypass destinations","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you want or need to use a fully-qualified domain name (FQDN) when specifying a         bypass destination, you can enable DNS lookup for bypass. An FQDN may be necessary if the         bypass destination IP is not static.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/bypass_enable_dns.html","attributes":{"data-id":"bypass_enable_dns"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"bypass_enable_dns-d10823e11306","topics":[]},{"title":"<span class=\"ph\">Airwall Edge Service<\/span> High Availability (HA)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">High Availability (HA) <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span> provide hardware   redundancy in a hot-standby mode. <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span> installed in an HA   configuration maintain a heartbeat on a dedicated Ethernet link where only the current primary is   participating in overlay network communications. If the primary fails to send heartbeat messages   to the secondary, the secondary takes over <span class=\"ph\">overlay<\/span> network communications   for the HA pair.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/hip_ha_overview.html","attributes":{"data-id":"hip_ha_overview"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"hip_ha_overview-d10823e11328","next":"hip_ha_overview-d10823e11328"},{"title":"One-arm mode","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can configure an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> to use a         single network connection in cases where you want to prevent common routing errors caused by         multiple interfaces.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/one_arm_mode.html","attributes":{"data-id":"one_arm_mode"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"one_arm_mode-d10823e11397","next":"one_arm_mode-d10823e11397"},{"title":"Network address translation (NAT)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Network Address Translation (NAT) translates an IP address in one network to a         different IP address in another network. The two IP addresses are referred to as the         External IP address and the Internal IP address. The External IP address is the IP address         of the device in the overlay network and the Internal IP address is the actual IP address of         the device.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/hip_config_nat.html","attributes":{"data-id":"hip_config_nat"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"hip_config_nat-d10823e11426","topics":[]},{"title":"Encryption and tunnel compression on an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span>","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can change the encryption or compression of <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateways<\/span>.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/hip_encrypt_comp.html","attributes":{"data-id":"hip_encrypt_comp"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"hip_encrypt_comp-d10823e11445","topics":[]},{"title":"Protected devices with static routing","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can configure static routing for protected devices with IP addresses not directly         connected to an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span>.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/dev_dhcp_config.html","attributes":{"data-id":"dev_dhcp_config"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"dev_dhcp_config-d10823e11472","topics":[]},{"title":"Protected devices with DHCP","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have protected devices that use DHCP to obtain an IP address, you need to         configure DHCP on the <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> that protects         that device.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/dev_static_config.html","attributes":{"data-id":"dev_dhcp_static"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"dev_dhcp_static-d10823e11498","topics":[]},{"title":"DHCP relay on an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span>","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have protected devices that use DHCP to obtain an IP address, you can         configure the <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span>         to relay the DHCP address to your DHCP server.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/aw_relay_dhcp.html","attributes":{"data-id":"untitled1"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"untitled1-d10823e11523","topics":[]},{"title":"Limit Device Traffic on an <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> with Port Filtering ","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use  <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> port filtering to limit what traffic can pass over an Overlay based on TCP\/UDP Ports. With     port filtering enabled, all communication from remote to local devices is disabled, and you     create custom rules to tell the local <span class=\"ph\">Airwall Gateway<\/span> what to allow as     incoming connections to local devices.<\/p>","href":"content\/topics\/aw_limit_traffic_port_filter.html","attributes":{"data-id":"custom_firewall_rules"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"custom_firewall_rules-d10823e11550","next":"custom_firewall_rules-d10823e11550"},{"title":"Spanning Tree Protocol on the <span class=\"ph\">Overlay<\/span> Network","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\"\/>","href":"content\/topics\/hip_spanning.html","attributes":{"data-id":"hip_spanning"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"hip_spanning-d10823e11594","topics":[]}]});